column42: This spawner goes to the area table to determine which monster spawner to use, and which monster spawn row to use.
This row goes to the area table to find which monster spawner to use, but uses the monster spawn row defined in cell

This does not use the area table for either the spawner or the spawn table row, they are both overridden.  In order to populate the monster spawner, right-click on it, say "Copy Reference", paste that into the location and then add _C before the closing quote.  Note that the two are separated by a pipe.

This uses the area table for the spawn table row, but overriddes the spawner.  In order to populate the monster spawner, right-click on it, say "Copy Reference", paste that into the location and then add _C before the closing quote.  Note that there is a pipe as the first character.

This will spawn the given hazard for the specified duration.  To set the hazard, right-click on the hazard->Copy Reference, then paste into the cell and add _C before the closing quote.  Hazards require a duration.  To set the duration, add a pipe after the hazard, then put in the duration.
